WEBVTT

00:10.552 --> 00:11.803
♪ You could do it solo ♪

00:11.803 --> 00:13.889
♪ But then you'd be all by yourself ♪

00:13.889 --> 00:16.600
♪ Yo! So, it'd be more fun
To share this one ♪

00:16.600 --> 00:17.935
♪ With someone else ♪

00:17.935 --> 00:21.855
♪ Together we will soar
Across the sky and beyond ♪

00:21.855 --> 00:23.065
♪ So turn up your voice ♪

00:23.857 --> 00:25.984
♪ Stand up and sing along ♪

00:25.984 --> 00:26.985
♪ All different voices ♪

00:26.985 --> 00:27.861
♪ Everybody now! ♪

00:27.861 --> 00:29.446
♪ Our melodies ringing ♪

00:29.446 --> 00:31.031
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪

00:31.240 --> 00:33.200
♪ Yeah, we're livin' in harmony ♪

00:33.200 --> 00:37.079
♪ Our song is much stronger
With every troll singing ♪

00:37.079 --> 00:39.498
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪♪

00:44.920 --> 00:46.213
‐ Hmm.

00:46.672 --> 00:48.966
Ha, ha! Take that!

00:50.968 --> 00:52.135
‐ Hmmm.

00:56.181 --> 00:58.809
‐ Huh… I just might be terrible at this.

01:00.060 --> 01:01.019
‐ Wha…?
‐ Wha…?

01:03.730 --> 01:05.190
‐ Um… who is that standing

01:05.190 --> 01:08.026
in all that professional
backlighting and stage fog?

01:09.653 --> 01:12.739
‐ Annyunghaseyo! We are K‐Pop Trolls!

01:14.866 --> 01:17.077
I'm Bi‐Na, "The Sweet One."

01:18.287 --> 01:20.747
‐ I'm Young, "The Feisty One."

01:22.457 --> 01:24.001
‐ And I'm Min,

01:24.001 --> 01:26.003
"The One Who Doesn't Have a Thing Yet…

01:27.045 --> 01:28.255
but I'm working on it!"

01:36.930 --> 01:39.725
[ singing in Korean ]

01:39.725 --> 01:41.476
♪ Oh, I love it, yeah, I love it ♪

01:41.476 --> 01:44.187
[ singing in Korean ]

01:44.187 --> 01:45.939
♪ Always gonna make it shine ♪

01:46.148 --> 01:50.777
[ singing in Korean ]

01:52.779 --> 01:54.364
♪ It's time to party ♪

01:54.364 --> 01:59.077
[ singing in Korean ]

01:59.077 --> 02:00.662
♪ Oh, no, don't let it stop ♪

02:00.662 --> 02:04.041
[ singing in Korean ]

02:04.041 --> 02:06.043
♪ Move your body, body ♪

02:06.043 --> 02:11.715
[ singing in Korean ]

02:11.715 --> 02:15.302
♪ Cuz I got it, got it
Make your heart go ♪

02:15.302 --> 02:17.137
♪ Go K‐poppin'
Yeah! ♪

02:17.137 --> 02:20.265
[ singing in Korean ]

02:20.557 --> 02:22.934
♪ You gotta K‐k‐krush on it ♪

02:22.934 --> 02:24.895
♪ No, you can't stop it! No! ♪

02:24.895 --> 02:28.106
[ singing in Korean ]

02:28.106 --> 02:28.982
♪ K‐k‐krush! ♪♪

02:28.982 --> 02:31.902
[ singing in Korean ]

02:33.403 --> 02:37.491
‐ That song was amazing!
I couldn't stop tapping my toes!

02:37.491 --> 02:38.492
‐ Correct!

02:38.492 --> 02:41.119
No one can resist shaking
their shimmy to K‐Pop!

02:41.119 --> 02:41.995
[ chuckles ]

02:41.995 --> 02:44.748
‐ Just like we can't resist
a dance challenge.

02:45.123 --> 02:47.250
Are you looking for a dance challenge?

02:48.126 --> 02:49.920
‐ Uh, maybe later?

02:49.920 --> 02:50.962
‐ If that's okay.

02:51.880 --> 02:53.090
‐ A‐OK‐pop.

02:54.132 --> 02:56.927
‐ So, K‐Pop Trolls!
What brings you to TrollsTopia?

02:56.927 --> 02:59.054
‐ We're here on a Trolls‐finding mission.

02:59.054 --> 03:00.097
[ chuckles ]

03:00.097 --> 03:02.974
See, we kinda have a knack
for Trolls‐finding.

03:02.974 --> 03:04.101
It's really fun!

03:04.685 --> 03:06.687
‐ Yeah, it's so fun,

03:06.687 --> 03:08.980
we shouldn't even call it
"Trolls‐finding,"

03:08.980 --> 03:11.733
we should call it "Trolls‐funning!"

03:11.733 --> 03:12.818
[ chuckles ]

03:15.862 --> 03:19.157
Okay, apparently I'm not the "Funny One."

03:19.741 --> 03:21.159
‐ Enough chit chat!

03:21.159 --> 03:23.370
We were sent here to find
a certain TrollsTopian

03:23.370 --> 03:25.664
about some unfinished business.

03:26.123 --> 03:29.501
‐ A year ago, this Troll was losing
a round of checkers

03:29.501 --> 03:33.797
when he committed one of the greatest
misdeeds known to Trollskind.

03:33.964 --> 03:38.927
He threw down his hat, stomped away
and left the game unfinished.

03:39.219 --> 03:41.054
‐ Y‐you don't mean…

03:41.638 --> 03:44.182
‐ That's right. We're looking for…

03:44.975 --> 03:47.227
a "not‐so‐good‐sport."

03:49.229 --> 03:51.022
‐ No. It can't be.

03:51.022 --> 03:53.859
All TrollsTopians practice
good sportsmanship!

03:54.025 --> 03:57.112
We even have a fun sheriff,
Gust Tumbleweed, to make sure of it!

03:57.821 --> 04:01.575
‐ Well, that's ironic,
because Gust Tumbleweed…

04:01.783 --> 04:04.619
‐ Is the Troll we're looking for!

04:08.081 --> 04:11.209
‐ Huh, I guess I'm not
"The Artistic One" either.

04:11.209 --> 04:14.004
But yeah, Gust Tumbleweed
is the Troll we're looking for.

04:14.254 --> 04:15.422
[ gasp ]

04:16.339 --> 04:19.259
‐ I'm sure that we can
sort all this out, ladies.

04:19.259 --> 04:21.887
There's no way Gust did
what you say he did.

04:22.053 --> 04:23.096
Gust?

04:23.889 --> 04:25.098
HOLLY:
Where is he?

04:27.392 --> 04:28.185
‐ Hmm.

04:30.395 --> 04:32.898
Looks like he heard
we were in town and ran,

04:32.898 --> 04:34.441
halfway through his doughnut.

04:34.441 --> 04:36.109
But he left a trail.

04:39.154 --> 04:41.698
Hmm. Powdered sugar's still fresh.

04:41.698 --> 04:42.657
This way!

04:46.912 --> 04:47.913
GUST:
Are they gone?

04:48.205 --> 04:49.247
[ screaming ]

04:51.249 --> 04:53.460
‐ Gust, wh‐what's going on?

04:53.460 --> 04:56.671
Why do those Trolls Finders
think you walked away from a game?

04:56.922 --> 05:00.926
‐ Well, Queen Poppy,
because technically, I did.

05:00.926 --> 05:01.843
[ gasp ]

05:01.843 --> 05:02.636
‐ No…

05:03.053 --> 05:04.679
‐ But for a very good reason.

05:05.013 --> 05:07.474
You see, the Troll
I was playin' against was…

05:08.183 --> 05:09.935
Cheatin' Charlie.

05:10.310 --> 05:14.523
‐ Wait, am I to assume from context clues
that this Charlie was…

05:15.273 --> 05:16.274
cheatin'?

05:16.733 --> 05:18.318
‐ Indeed he was.

05:18.318 --> 05:21.238
And the longer we played,
the worse it got.

05:21.446 --> 05:24.908
'Til finally I had no choice
but to walk away.

05:25.283 --> 05:28.453
'Cuz as we all know,
if a game ain't fair…

05:28.954 --> 05:31.206
‐ …a game ain't fun.
‐ …a game ain't fun.

05:31.665 --> 05:33.083
‐ Don't you worry, Gust.

05:33.333 --> 05:36.670
We just need to get you outta town
until the K‐Pop Trolls leave.

05:36.878 --> 05:40.131
‐ Yeah, I mean,
they can't search for you forever.

05:40.715 --> 05:44.719
‐ We will search for Gust Tumbleweed
forever if we have to!

05:45.095 --> 05:48.431
So if you know where he is,
you might as well spill the glitter.

05:48.765 --> 05:50.100
‐ Be your best friend!

05:50.684 --> 05:51.685
‐ Yiah!

05:53.937 --> 05:55.188
‐ Hmm.
‐ Hmm.

05:57.107 --> 05:58.358
‐ Oh, sorry, Poppy,

05:58.358 --> 06:01.027
but can we take a peek
in your barrels, please?

06:01.027 --> 06:03.947
You would not believe where Trolls
try to hide sometimes.

06:05.115 --> 06:07.200
‐ Uh…

06:09.119 --> 06:11.705
Okay… but I hope you have all day.

06:11.705 --> 06:13.582
There are a lot of 'em.

06:16.543 --> 06:20.005
‐ Oh, not a problem.
If he's here, we'll find him.

06:20.380 --> 06:21.464
‐ One!
‐ Two!

06:21.464 --> 06:22.340
‐ Three!

06:24.175 --> 06:25.135
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

06:27.345 --> 06:28.305
‐ Oh, no.

06:28.597 --> 06:31.558
‐ No one can resist
shakin' their shimmy to K‐Pop.

06:31.975 --> 06:32.893
‐ Huh?

06:32.893 --> 06:35.729
M‐my shimmy… it's shakin'!

06:37.147 --> 06:40.442
♪ Meolibuteo bal kkeutkkaji nolaboja ♪

06:40.442 --> 06:43.528
♪ Move your body, body gyesog ♪

06:43.528 --> 06:44.863
♪ Wo‐oh‐oh ♪

06:44.863 --> 06:48.199
♪ Eodigado nan jeoldae gijugjianh‐a ♪

06:48.199 --> 06:50.160
♪ Cuz I got it, got it ♪

06:50.160 --> 06:51.953
♪ Make your heart go… ♪♪

06:54.873 --> 06:55.957
‐ Dance Off!

06:56.291 --> 06:57.083
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

06:57.375 --> 07:00.295
‐ We challenge you to a Dance Off!

07:00.295 --> 07:01.296
‐ We do?

07:02.505 --> 07:05.383
‐ You remembered
our weakness for dance offs.

07:05.383 --> 07:07.761
And as you know
we cannot let a challenge go…

07:08.178 --> 07:09.638
undancered!

07:10.388 --> 07:11.765
VIDEO GAME VOICE:
<i>Dance off!</i>

07:16.853 --> 07:18.813
<i>Smooth moves!</i>

07:24.235 --> 07:25.695
<i>Epic Performance!</i>

07:26.196 --> 07:27.238
TROLLS:
Wow!

07:34.663 --> 07:35.580
‐ Meomchwo!

07:35.914 --> 07:37.248
VIDEO GAME VOICE:
<i>Busted!</i>

07:37.791 --> 07:39.000
[ laughing ]

07:39.000 --> 07:41.294
[ cheering and laughing ]

07:41.294 --> 07:44.422
‐ Guys, I realized
they were trying to distract us!

07:44.422 --> 07:46.675
It turns out, I'm "The Clever One!"

07:48.593 --> 07:51.179
‐ As the official "Clever One,"
I gotta say,

07:51.179 --> 07:53.682
we need to stop sharing
our weakness for dance‐offs

07:53.682 --> 07:55.392
every time we meet someone new.

07:55.600 --> 07:57.686
VIDEO GAME VOICE:
<i>She makes a good point!</i>

07:57.894 --> 07:59.229
‐ Mmm‐hmm.
‐ Mmm‐hmm.

07:59.229 --> 08:02.482
‐ Gust Tumbleweed,
a Troll in Lonesome Flats

08:02.482 --> 08:06.486
requests you to return
to finish your game.

08:06.486 --> 08:08.363
‐ Pretty, pretty please?

08:08.363 --> 08:09.656
‐ Uh… eh…

08:10.281 --> 08:14.452
‐ No, K‐Poppers, listen.
Gust is not a not‐so‐good‐sport!

08:14.452 --> 08:17.497
He had to walk away from that game,
because the other Troll…

08:17.497 --> 08:18.707
was cheatin'.

08:18.957 --> 08:19.749
[ gasp ]

08:19.749 --> 08:20.875
‐ You're sure?

08:21.418 --> 08:22.711
‐ Absolutely.

08:22.711 --> 08:26.423
And as every Troll here knows,
if a game ain't fair…

08:26.506 --> 08:28.675
‐ …a game ain't fun.
‐ …a game ain't fun.

08:29.426 --> 08:32.262
‐ Well, this changes everything.

08:32.387 --> 08:34.222
‐ You mean…?
MIN: Yes.

08:34.431 --> 08:39.310
No Troll should leave a game unfinished,
but you do have a very good excuse.

08:39.644 --> 08:40.437
[ sighs ]

08:40.603 --> 08:42.397
‐ Thank you kindly.

08:42.397 --> 08:43.565
And I promise you,

08:43.565 --> 08:46.568
I will never walk away
from a game like I did

08:46.568 --> 08:48.987
with Cheatin' Charlie ever again.

08:49.863 --> 08:50.864
MIN:
Um,

08:51.364 --> 08:54.534
we weren't sent here
by a Troll named Charlie.

08:55.702 --> 08:59.414
‐ Wait, so you walked away
from two games?

08:59.706 --> 09:01.666
VIDEO GAME VOICE:
<i>Interesting twist!</i>

09:02.125 --> 09:03.835
‐ Gust, what is this?

09:03.835 --> 09:06.046
‐ I‐I surely don't know.

09:06.046 --> 09:07.338
Who was it that sent ya?

09:07.505 --> 09:09.340
‐ A Troll named Chester.

09:09.340 --> 09:12.177
‐ You mean Cheatin' Chester?

09:12.343 --> 09:13.303
[ everyone gasps ]

09:13.303 --> 09:16.264
‐ No, wait a minute…

09:16.473 --> 09:18.933
‐ N‐no, you have to understand.

09:19.100 --> 09:22.395
Cheatin' Chester cheats even worse
than Cheatin' Charlie!

09:22.479 --> 09:23.897
‐ I dunno…

09:23.897 --> 09:26.941
VIDEO GAME VOICE:
<i>Yeah, something smells fishy!</i>

09:27.525 --> 09:28.985
‐ Hold on, guys.

09:30.487 --> 09:34.365
I'll admit this is weird,
but we shouldn't jump to conclusions

09:34.365 --> 09:37.327
just because he walked away
from a couple of games.

09:37.327 --> 09:38.203
‐ Yeah!

09:38.203 --> 09:40.371
Besides, you can't believe a word

09:40.371 --> 09:42.957
that comes out of the mouth
of Cheatin' Chelsea!

09:42.957 --> 09:43.750
[ gasp ]

09:44.334 --> 09:45.376
‐ Wait, who?

09:45.376 --> 09:47.545
‐ Hey, I know Cheatin' Chelsea.

09:47.545 --> 09:49.881
And her name's just Chelsea!

09:50.006 --> 09:52.342
What is that, three games
you walked away from?

09:52.342 --> 09:56.012
‐ Gust, I want to believe you,
but it's starting to feel

09:56.012 --> 09:59.349
like you just don't like losing,
so whenever you do,

09:59.349 --> 10:01.976
you call the other Troll
a cheater and walk away.

10:01.976 --> 10:03.520
‐ Mm‐hmm!
‐ Mm‐hmm!

10:03.520 --> 10:06.356
[ speaking at the same time ]

10:06.356 --> 10:08.358
‐ No. Th‐that's not it…

10:11.069 --> 10:13.822
Oh, I see how it is.

10:14.155 --> 10:16.407
You think I'm a not‐so‐good sport,

10:16.407 --> 10:21.079
despite my perfectly good explanations
to the contrary, is that it?

10:21.579 --> 10:26.918
Well fine, if y'all ain't gonna be fair,
then I'm leavin'!

10:32.423 --> 10:33.466
Oh…

10:34.050 --> 10:35.552
Oh, oh my…

10:38.847 --> 10:42.433
I really am a not‐so‐good‐sport…

10:43.434 --> 10:44.561
'Scuse me.

10:44.769 --> 10:48.690
If ya'll will oblige me,
I got some thinkin' to do…

10:52.110 --> 10:55.405
VIDEO GAME VOICE: <i>There's strength</i>
<i>in admitting your mistakes!</i>

10:55.405 --> 10:56.865
‐ Enough!
‐ Not helping!

10:59.325 --> 11:00.243
‐ Gust?

11:00.243 --> 11:02.662
‐ You headin' back
to Lonesome Flats, sugar?

11:02.662 --> 11:04.289
‐ Just for a few days.

11:04.289 --> 11:06.833
I realized that the only
sportsmanly thing to do

11:06.833 --> 11:09.794
is to finish those games, win or lose.

11:10.211 --> 11:12.172
Thank you for helping me see that.

11:13.798 --> 11:17.260
‐ Well, it's been so much fun,
TrollsTopia.

11:17.260 --> 11:19.637
But I'm afraid it's time for us to go.

11:20.430 --> 11:21.431
[ Min sniffles ]

11:22.223 --> 11:24.309
‐ Min, you okay?

11:24.642 --> 11:27.103
‐ Uh‐huh. It just turns out…

11:27.395 --> 11:31.900
I'm actually "The One Who Has
a Hard Time Saying Goodbye."

11:33.818 --> 11:35.028
EVERYONE:
Aww.

11:42.702 --> 11:45.246
[ Poppy laughing ]

11:48.458 --> 11:51.669
‐ Run for your lives!
It's a monster ya'll!

11:51.669 --> 11:54.797
‐ Listen to the troll with the big hair,
this is not a drill!

11:54.797 --> 11:56.716
[ Holly and Val screaming ]

11:57.467 --> 12:00.303
‐ Holly! Val! What? A monster?

12:00.511 --> 12:03.139
‐ We were playin'
a rousing game of Holly Ball.

12:03.556 --> 12:06.601
Basically just like Volley Ball,
except I'm involved.

12:06.726 --> 12:07.518
Anyway…

12:08.353 --> 12:13.274
<i>I musta put a little too much woo‐hoo</i>
<i>in my follow through, 'cuz…</i>

12:13.691 --> 12:14.901
Woo‐hoo!

12:17.111 --> 12:20.531
VAL: <i>We wound up deeper in the Woods</i>
<i>than we've ever been before.</i>

12:21.741 --> 12:22.742
[ Val and Holly gasp ]

12:22.742 --> 12:24.744
<i>And that's where we saw it…</i>

12:24.911 --> 12:27.705
<i>It was big! And it was mean!</i>

12:28.748 --> 12:29.582
[ gasp ]

12:29.999 --> 12:32.460
HOLLY:
<i>And I know it's not Trolly</i>

12:32.460 --> 12:34.921
<i>to pass judgment</i>
<i>on another's appearance but…</i>

12:34.921 --> 12:35.713
[ Holly chilled ]

12:36.339 --> 12:38.758
…it's clothes were so tacky.

12:38.758 --> 12:40.301
[ Trolls startle ]

12:40.718 --> 12:44.722
‐ Okay. First of all, pencil me in
for the next round of Holly Ball,

12:44.722 --> 12:46.683
that game sounds amazing.

12:46.683 --> 12:49.727
And second: you didn't see a monster!

12:49.727 --> 12:51.187
You saw a Bergen!

12:51.187 --> 12:53.564
And Bergens are actually really nice.

12:53.564 --> 12:55.984
‐ I dunno, Poppy, you didn't see him.

12:56.150 --> 12:59.570
He had this, "I'd very much like
to eat a Troll" look in his eye.

12:59.570 --> 13:00.697
Like this.

13:01.614 --> 13:03.366
[ Trolls bigger startle ]

13:04.242 --> 13:08.454
‐ Guys, I'm telling you,
Bergens do not eat Trolls…

13:08.579 --> 13:09.956
and I'll prove it.

13:09.956 --> 13:13.876
Take me to this "monster"
and I'll show you how kind they are.

13:13.876 --> 13:15.336
Can you retrace your steps?

13:15.753 --> 13:18.673
‐ Well. I went woo‐hoo and then…

13:22.719 --> 13:23.594
That way.

13:24.887 --> 13:26.639
[ Holly and Val cowering ]

13:27.098 --> 13:28.891
‐ Oh, man, there he is.

13:29.142 --> 13:32.020
‐ Every hair on my head
is standin' on the end.

13:32.603 --> 13:35.148
And that ain't just
the hairspray talkin', ya'll.

13:35.148 --> 13:37.233
‐ Okay. Great! Let's go say hello!

13:37.233 --> 13:38.818
‐ Wait!
‐ Poppy, no!

13:39.610 --> 13:41.154
‐ Hi! I'm Poppy!

13:42.989 --> 13:44.824
[ Val and Holly cowering ]

13:48.161 --> 13:49.454
How are you today?

13:52.832 --> 13:58.046
‐ Well, better now that you're here,
you precious pink puff of perfection!

13:58.755 --> 13:59.797
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

13:59.797 --> 14:01.340
‐ The name's Barnald!

14:01.632 --> 14:03.801
‐ Nice to meet you, Barnald!

14:03.801 --> 14:06.012
These are my friends, Holly and Val!

14:06.679 --> 14:07.722
[ Holly and Val startle ]

14:08.347 --> 14:09.474
[ Poppy chuckling ]

14:09.474 --> 14:10.683
Excuse me.

14:10.975 --> 14:14.270
Will you two please come out here
and begin a journey of friendship

14:14.270 --> 14:15.772
that will last a lifetime?

14:15.938 --> 14:17.690
‐ Eh, I don't know.

14:17.690 --> 14:19.442
I just don't think I trust that guy.

14:19.442 --> 14:21.694
‐ He's wearin' plaid, Poppy!

14:21.694 --> 14:22.820
Plaid!

14:22.820 --> 14:24.113
‐ Knock, knock!

14:24.530 --> 14:25.490
Me again.

14:25.698 --> 14:28.659
Sorry to interrupt,
but I sure would be as pleased

14:28.659 --> 14:31.704
as puffalo punch
if you two would come out.

14:31.704 --> 14:35.875
We can all go back
to my humble cottage, hmm?

14:36.417 --> 14:38.503
‐ Inviting us back to his cottage?

14:38.795 --> 14:40.713
Aw, what a sweet gesture!

14:40.713 --> 14:44.592
I mean, how not‐eat‐Trollsy
is this guy, eh?

14:44.842 --> 14:49.055
‐ Oh, no, I'm definitely gonna eat'cha!

14:49.055 --> 14:50.014
‐ What?

14:50.014 --> 14:51.390
[ screaming ]

14:51.724 --> 14:54.060
‐ Wow! You sure showed us, Popsqueak.

14:54.477 --> 14:55.853
‐ I knew it!

14:55.853 --> 14:59.524
He was just puttin' on
that sweet folksy accent to trick us!

14:59.774 --> 15:02.735
‐ Oh, no, no, that's just how I talk.

15:02.735 --> 15:03.861
But don't let it fool ya!

15:03.861 --> 15:07.365
I'm just as mean n' stinky
as the next Bergen!

15:11.369 --> 15:12.286
[ chuckles ]

15:12.286 --> 15:14.705
‐ Barnald, this must be a mistake.

15:14.705 --> 15:16.833
Bergens don't eat Trolls anymore.

15:17.458 --> 15:20.753
‐ Umm… since when?

15:20.920 --> 15:24.340
‐ Since all the Trolls and the Bergens
sang and danced together

15:24.340 --> 15:27.885
and you learned that true happiness
comes from within, remember?

15:30.429 --> 15:35.268
‐ Oh, my, that sounds
like a hum‐doozy of a tall tale!

15:35.768 --> 15:38.896
But I can't say I'm buyin'
what you're sellin', little morsel!

15:39.897 --> 15:42.859
Shucks, I haven't lived
in Bergen Town for years

15:42.859 --> 15:45.111
but I'll be dipped if I'm gonna believe

15:45.111 --> 15:47.947
that Bergens would just up
and change their way of life

15:47.947 --> 15:50.158
cuz you sang 'em a song.

15:50.158 --> 15:51.576
[ laughing ]

15:51.951 --> 15:54.120
‐ It was a really good song.

15:54.745 --> 15:58.499
‐ Well, in any case,
now that you're here,

15:58.708 --> 16:02.837
I know someone who's going to have
a very tasty Trollstice next month.

16:03.254 --> 16:05.047
Spoiler alert it's me!

16:05.047 --> 16:06.340
[ laughing ]

16:06.340 --> 16:07.675
Good, Barnald!

16:07.675 --> 16:10.052
‐ Okay, how're we bustin'
outta this joint?

16:10.261 --> 16:11.137
‐ Simple.

16:11.137 --> 16:13.764
We need to disorient him
while we make our escape.

16:13.764 --> 16:18.311
I suggest giving his nose hairs,
a great big yank!

16:18.728 --> 16:20.146
‐ Ew!

16:20.605 --> 16:22.815
But yes!

16:22.815 --> 16:24.150
POPPY: No!
‐ Huh?

16:24.150 --> 16:25.776
‐ No nose hairs, guys!

16:25.776 --> 16:30.573
Barnald may not be a friendly Bergen yet,
but with our help he will be.

16:30.948 --> 16:33.409
‐ You still think
that he's gonna be nice to us?

16:33.409 --> 16:35.953
‐ Poppy, I know you got a big heart,

16:35.953 --> 16:38.456
but you gotta wake up
and smell what's for dinner…

16:38.456 --> 16:39.624
'cuz it's us!

16:39.624 --> 16:43.753
‐ Guys, I promise you,
we will get out of this cottage.

16:43.961 --> 16:48.716
And our soon‐to‐ be new best friend
Barnald is gonna open the door for us.

16:54.597 --> 16:57.433
Hey, Barnald! Yoo‐hoo!
‐ Huh?

16:57.892 --> 17:01.354
Well, how can I help you,
my lil' explosion of flavor?

17:01.646 --> 17:04.857
‐ Y'know, I'll bet that if you and I
got to know each other

17:04.857 --> 17:07.860
you'd realize we have a lot more
in common than you think.

17:07.860 --> 17:08.903
‐ Hm…

17:09.070 --> 17:12.156
‐ Tell us about yourself, Barnald.
What do you like to do?

17:12.907 --> 17:14.075
‐ Hmm…

17:14.075 --> 17:15.159
Cook Trolls!

17:16.202 --> 17:17.411
‐ Keep going.

17:17.995 --> 17:22.416
‐ Curl up with a good book
in which the protagonist eats Trolls!

17:22.416 --> 17:23.542
[ Poppy startling ]

17:23.542 --> 17:26.879
‐ Hey, look at that… he's a reader.

17:26.879 --> 17:28.839
C'mon, Barnald, work with me here.

17:29.006 --> 17:30.174
‐ Huh…

17:30.841 --> 17:32.760
Did I mention "eatin' Trolls"?

17:34.178 --> 17:36.055
‐ You did, Barnald. You did.

17:42.812 --> 17:44.063
‐ Yeowch‐a!

17:44.605 --> 17:46.440
Oh, that hurts!

17:46.941 --> 17:48.693
‐ Ah, ha! Now's my chance.

17:48.943 --> 17:51.529
A kind gesture will get
this friendship rolling.

17:58.995 --> 17:59.870
[ Barnald gasps ]

18:00.621 --> 18:01.872
There you go, Barnald!

18:02.415 --> 18:04.667
‐ Oh… Well now!

18:04.667 --> 18:06.794
Isn't that just all sorts of better!

18:07.044 --> 18:08.629
Thank you, little Troll.

18:09.046 --> 18:11.090
You have truly done me a kindness.

18:14.927 --> 18:18.264
Why, if you hadn't demonstrated
that you can get outta my Troll cage,

18:18.264 --> 18:20.891
you and your friends
would've been able to escape!

18:24.186 --> 18:25.229
[ Poppy chuckling ]

18:25.229 --> 18:26.147
‐ Poppy?

18:26.147 --> 18:29.233
I love ya.
But I just can't even right now.

18:29.483 --> 18:32.320
I just can't even!

18:32.486 --> 18:34.530
‐ Actually, I think Barnald and I

18:34.530 --> 18:36.991
were starting to make
a real connection there.

18:36.991 --> 18:39.035
You know, before he locked us
in a metal box.

18:39.368 --> 18:43.039
‐ Ugh, Poppy, that Bergen
ain't ever gonna change.

18:43.039 --> 18:43.914
‐ Agreed.

18:43.914 --> 18:48.628
Now let's trick him into opening this box,
grab life by the nose hairs and yank!

18:49.003 --> 18:51.672
‐ No! I am not giving up on Barnald.

18:51.672 --> 18:54.133
We can change him, I know it.

18:54.884 --> 18:55.760
[ knocking ]

18:55.760 --> 18:56.552
‐ Huh?

19:01.932 --> 19:04.310
♪ Life's sweeter when you got friends ♪

19:04.894 --> 19:06.062
♪ No doubt about it ♪

19:06.520 --> 19:08.898
♪ Together until the end ♪

19:09.315 --> 19:10.816
♪ Can't live without 'em ♪

19:11.150 --> 19:13.486
♪ We'll adventure together ♪

19:13.736 --> 19:15.821
♪ Ain't a storm we can't weather ♪

19:16.113 --> 19:20.159
♪ Live it up, hold it down
And we'll do it forever ♪

19:20.159 --> 19:22.620
♪ Take a chance maybe ♪

19:22.620 --> 19:24.914
♪ And I know you'll see ♪

19:24.914 --> 19:28.751
♪ How amazing life could be ♪

19:28.751 --> 19:30.169
♪ As best friends with me ♪

19:30.378 --> 19:34.090
♪ Just know, everywhere you go ♪

19:34.090 --> 19:37.968
♪ I'll be right there following ♪

19:37.968 --> 19:39.553
♪ Be best friends with me! ♪♪

19:41.472 --> 19:42.390
[ Barnald gasping ]

19:42.598 --> 19:44.308
‐ That‐that song…

19:44.767 --> 19:47.103
I didn't think music
could make me feel this way!

19:47.103 --> 19:50.147
I can't believe this,
but this changes everything!

19:50.231 --> 19:51.023
[ Poppy gasps ]

19:51.857 --> 19:54.068
I can't eat you on Trollstice.

19:54.318 --> 19:55.236
‐ You can't?

19:55.611 --> 19:56.529
‐ No.

19:57.154 --> 19:58.989
I have to eat'cha right now!

19:58.989 --> 20:00.157
‐ What?

20:00.324 --> 20:01.367
‐ Oh, yes.

20:01.367 --> 20:03.994
That song was just so dreadfully cheerful.

20:04.161 --> 20:06.247
I can't risk listening to that again.

20:06.539 --> 20:10.000
Also, it was a little pitchy.

20:11.168 --> 20:12.378
‐ Pitchy?

20:12.712 --> 20:14.171
Barnald, no,

20:14.338 --> 20:16.006
it's not supposed to be like this.

20:16.006 --> 20:18.092
You're a nice Bergen, deep down‐‐

20:18.092 --> 20:19.176
Ah!

20:22.430 --> 20:23.848
VAL: Poppy!
Holly: Poppy!

20:24.390 --> 20:26.600
‐ Please, get outta there!

20:26.600 --> 20:28.144
‐ You've gotta listen to us.

20:28.227 --> 20:29.437
Run!

20:29.937 --> 20:31.397
HOLLY:
Poppy, run!

20:31.397 --> 20:32.815
You gotta go, girl!

20:32.982 --> 20:35.025
‐ No. I'm not running.

20:36.444 --> 20:37.820
[ Holly and Val groaning ]

20:39.155 --> 20:41.240
Because there's good in you, Barnald.

20:41.615 --> 20:43.701
And I know that you're not
going to eat me.

20:44.160 --> 20:45.786
‐ I‐I'm not?

20:46.162 --> 20:48.038
‐ Oh, no, no, no…

20:48.038 --> 20:49.081
‐ You won't do it.

20:51.125 --> 20:52.209
You won't do it.

20:55.880 --> 20:57.047
You won't do it.

20:57.214 --> 20:58.132
Ah!

20:58.132 --> 21:00.050
‐ Nope, I'm still gonna eat'cha.

21:01.677 --> 21:03.804
‐ No!
‐ No!

21:04.180 --> 21:05.097
‐ Yeah, I know.

21:05.347 --> 21:07.475
I just needed to get
close enough to do this!

21:07.767 --> 21:10.436
[ Barnald howling ]

21:11.479 --> 21:13.439
‐ It stings like the dickens!

21:14.064 --> 21:16.025
Heavens to mercy!

21:16.025 --> 21:18.903
‐ I‐I didn't know she had it in her.

21:19.069 --> 21:20.529
‐ I've never been so proud.

21:23.115 --> 21:26.285
‐ Guys, I was totally wrong
and I should've listened to you!

21:26.285 --> 21:28.037
‐ It's okay, you can't help it!

21:28.162 --> 21:32.041
‐ Yeah, sugar, that's what makes you you,
now run, ya'll!

21:32.041 --> 21:34.210
[ screaming ]

21:38.714 --> 21:42.635
‐ Well, I was right about one thing.
He did open the door for us!

21:42.635 --> 21:44.220
[ Poppy, Val and Holly cheering ]

21:47.306 --> 21:49.058
‐ Hot dang, Poppy!

21:49.058 --> 21:51.393
I just about jumped right outta my hooves

21:51.393 --> 21:54.230
when I saw you danglin'
from that Bergen's sniffer!

21:54.480 --> 21:55.731
‐ Hey. Who am I?

21:57.441 --> 22:00.861
[ laughing ]

22:00.861 --> 22:02.947
Thanks for getting us outta there, Poppy.

22:02.947 --> 22:07.076
‐ And, I'm sorry you had to give up
on makin' friends with the Bergen.

22:07.535 --> 22:09.119
‐ Oh, I haven't given up.

22:09.119 --> 22:10.246
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

22:10.246 --> 22:13.332
‐ When I said that I see
the good in Barnald, I meant it.

22:13.707 --> 22:15.751
I'll change his mind about eating Trolls.

22:16.085 --> 22:18.546
It might just take
a little longer than I thought.

22:24.093 --> 22:25.427
‐ A tiny little letter?

22:26.512 --> 22:29.181
POPPY:
<i>Dear Barnald. How have you been?</i>

22:29.515 --> 22:32.226
<i>How are your nose hairs?</i>
<i>Better I hope.</i>

22:35.646 --> 22:37.147
‐ Yeah, I'm still gonna eat 'em.

22:38.315 --> 22:41.944
♪ Meolibuteo bal kkeutkkaji nolaboja ♪

22:41.944 --> 22:45.114
♪ Move your body, body gyesog ♪

22:45.114 --> 22:46.198
♪ Who‐oh‐oh ♪

22:46.198 --> 22:49.493
♪ Eodigado nan jeoldae gijugjianh‐a ♪

22:49.493 --> 22:53.205
♪ Cuz I got it, got it
Make your heart go ♪

22:53.205 --> 22:55.124
♪ Go K‐poppin
Yeah! ♪

22:55.124 --> 22:58.168
♪ Eum‐ag‐e banhaebanhae beolyeo ♪

22:58.168 --> 23:01.130
♪ You gotta K‐k‐krush on it ♪

23:01.130 --> 23:02.131
♪ K‐k‐krush! ♪

23:02.131 --> 23:04.592
♪ Michyeobeolyeo dum
Dum, dum, dum, dum ♪♪
